italic toggle="yes">n</italic> = 137) and ponies (<italic toggle="yes">n</italic> = 43) aged 3&#8211;28 years&#8221;.</p><p>The corrected sentence appears below:</p><p>&#8220;Researchers analyzed Oxspring radiographs of either the left or right front hoof from warmblood horses (<italic toggle="yes">n</italic> = 132) and ponies (<italic toggle="yes">n</italic> = 43) aged 3&#8211;28 years&#8221;.</p><p>The original article has been updated.</p></body><back><sec sec-type="disclaimer" id="s1"><title>Publisher's note</title><p>All claims expressed in this article are solely those of the authors and do not necessarily represent those of their affiliated organizations, or those of the publisher, the editors and the reviewers. Any product that may be evaluated in this article, or claim that may be made by its manufacturer, is not guaranteed or endorsed by the publisher.</p></sec></back></article></pmc-articleset>